<div id="comment_status_64109591" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64109591" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64109591" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64109591" name="comment_link_64109591" href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23173861&amp;cid=64109591" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64109591)" >Re:get rid of the tipped min wage and let tips com</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64109591" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64109591); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Informative)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~bsolar">bsolar</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~bsolar">( 1176767 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64109591">		
		on Wednesday December 27, 2023 @01:36PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23173861&amp;cid=64109591">#64109591</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64109591"><p><div class="quote"><p>Do you really think restaurants will start "paying a livable wage" just because tipping is eliminated?</p></div><p>Yes, since the minimum wage would still apply.</p><p>Currently for tipped employees the employer can pay a lower wage than the statutory minimum, but only if the tips make up for the difference. If the tips don't make up for the difference, the employer is required to increase the salary until the employee meets minimum wage.</p><p>If you remove tips, the employer would just pay minimum wage like normal and recoup the amount spent on wages by increasing the base price of the goods. The employee would receive at least minimum wage, or whatever they can negotiate as salary, and the customer would be billed service included.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64109591">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64109591" class="btn link" href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23173861&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64109591" onclick="D2.replyTo(64109591); return false;">Reply to This</a> <span class="ind"></span><a class="btn link" href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23173861&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;cid=64109493" onclick="return D2.selectParent(64109493)">Parent</a> 	<a href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
