		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64109563">The moment we(country) legally excluded waitstaff from a minimum wage, amended to set a lower minimum, we allowed it to become obligatory. There is more nuance to the problem, in that even if they're paid above minimum wage it may not be a livable wage for the area. As customers, we're not privy to that side of things. I'm not saying this to place blame/guilt on anyone in particular. Tipping is just a messy problem that we should get rid of.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64109563">
