	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64109909"><p>I understand the arguments for tipping (it inspires better service, it allows the company to pay less, etc.). But at it's heart, tipping in restaurants just doesn't make sense. Why should anyone's wage be tied to what I order? Is it any more work for the server to take my order for a steak that costs $40 and deliver it to the table that it is for a hamburger that costs $20? If I order water instead of a soda, why do they deserve to make less money? It makes absolutely no sense at all. To me, that is the big<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64109909">

